===Letters=== Editing and publication of [[Letters of Charles Dickens|Dickens's letters]] started in 1949 when publisher [[Rupert Hart-Davis]] persuaded [[Humphry House]] of [[Wadham College]], [[Oxford University|Oxford]], to edit a complete edition of the letters. House died suddenly aged 46 in 1955. However, the work continued, and by 1997 Volume 9 had been published.<ref> {{cite book |last=Hart-Davis |first=Rupert |title= Halfway to Heaven: Concluding memoirs of a literary life | year= 1998 |publisher= Sutton |location= Stroud, Gloucestershire | page= 42|isbn=0-7509-1837-3 }}</ref>
